    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-3784983">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-3784983">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,3784983)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-3784983">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/fieldstone" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1436137); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1436137&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250122" alt="fieldstone" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1436137)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/fieldstone" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1436137); return false;" >fieldstone</a></span> <span class="odate time_1525068637 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">30 Apr 2018 06:10</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3784983">
									

<p>You have a lot of good points here.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>If they're getting D-class by kidnapping, they'd have to come from the very fringes of society (an idea I'm <a href="/ethics">fond of</a> because it adds to the horror of the whole premise). Most anyone with an account on this site is too on-the-grid to disappear like that, so it makes sense that less realistic D-class backgrounds would be more relatable to writers and therefore show up a lot.</p>
<p>I can justify to myself that for the occasional job that needs a special skill set, they would resort to yanking a surgeon or mathematician or retired FBI agent into a van, investigation be damned - they can quash it if it somehow gets close to them. People from those backgrounds do go missing too, occasionally, and the Foundation would be able to target ones who have marital/legal/financial problems as a smokescreen and no loved ones to search for them.</p>
<p>I agree that most D-class would think they were actually doing something else - I imagine a lot of arrangements like the ones in <a href="/heart-in-the-hand-of-matter">heart in the hand of matter</a> or <a href="/boxes">boxes</a>. I also like the idea that there are dentist's offices or national parks or highway rest stops where people just like you and me are grabbed for quick tests and then amnesticized and released, with their death made to look like an accident if something goes wrong.</p>
<p>Like you said, none of it is truly realistic, and it all comes down to individual headcanon. I agree that the Foundation would put D-class into dangerous situations only when necessary - I just also imagine that the Foundation's world is so hostile that &quot;only when necessary&quot; still requires kidnapping and human sacrifice on a massive scale.</p>
<p>For what it's worth, that NCIC report said that over 99% of missing children are found in the first few hours, so that's nice to know.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

